row.activityName: Photo with a Message Photo Contest
row.photoDescription: 長者，無論貧或富，亦可能面臨著一個問題-子女無法在他們身邊照顧佢地。圖中的長者，家境不錯，老伴離去，其他家人移民外國無法在佢身邊，即使有個印傭照顧，亦不免會感到孤單。

row.activityName: Photo with a Message Photo Contest
row.photoDescription: 陳伯在七年前因中風而全身癱瘓，妻子是唯一的照顧者，她背負照顧的重擔，雖身心疲累，但由於政府對這類長者欠缺支援，故她每天只好帶著丈夫在鴨寮街的後巷開檔，白天收集舊二手物，深夜時份擺賣地攤，經營無牌小販。
row.photoTitle: Cheung Chi Wai, 1st Runner-up, Elderly-themed Group

row.activityName: Photo with a Message Photo Contest
row.photoDescription: This man represents many elderly in Hong Kong. Many of them are out in the streets asking for spare change. He did not only have any money, he did not have any legs either. The wheelchair on the background is what he uses to get to places. Elderly in Hong Kong are in need of special care and usually have problems with their financial status. Even at an old age, they face economical and health hardships.

row.activityName: Photo with a Message Photo Contest
row.photoDescription: One of my passions as a photographer is to use my pictures to showcase the different angles that are present within a society. Hong Kong is a rich society and beneath the glamor of it all there are still some social issues that require more attention. Even though Hong Kong has a strong social safety net in place, things like this provide a stark reminder that maybe not everyone has access to it or benefitted from it. The marginalized suffer as a consequence of a broken social contract.

row.activityName: Photo with a Message Photo Contest
row.photoDescription: I took this picture on the peak on Taiping Mountain. This view point is common, almost all of the travelers will take a picture at the same spot. However, when you amazed by the beautiful night view of Hong Kong, have you ever thought about the light pollution of Hong Kong? I used over expose and double expose techniques to show an uncommon view of Hong Kong, an over-exposed Hong Kong.

row.activityName: Photo with a Message Photo Contest
row.photoDescription: 學習 ﹣ 在2011年10月，公共屋村拍攝。當全城要求學生全能教育和怪獸家長的完美要求下，在這城市有誰在意一個單親家的小朋友的成長和學習。 沒有人体工學的書枱和座椅，也沒有教授級的名師補習，連家長也只顧自娛，他只能選擇奮鬥的道路。因為只有努力學習才擺脫生活的困景，也只有奮鬥才會走出父或母的舊路。

row.photoTitle: Our first student internship took place in Zhongshan Youth Social Innovation Park (SIP), in association with the Communist Youth League of Zhongshan, from 2 to 28 June 2013. Eight students were recruited (one student withdrew from the internship after one week and returned to Hong Kong due to health reason) to support and assist the daily operation of the SIP.\n By participating in the Project Flame Student Internship, student interns should be able to deepen their understanding of the ideas of social entrepreneurship and innovation in different contexts, and be equipped with relevant work experience and skills for their future.

row.activityName: Social Enterprise Study Trip in Singapore
row.photoTitle: On 14-18 July 2013, Project Flame, with the assistance and coordination of Singapore Social Innovation Park, organized a “Social Enterprise Study Tour” in Singapore as part of Project Flame’s Student SE Activities. 14 participating students visited 8 leading social enterprises, the Ministry of Family and Social Development of Singapore and the NUS Entrepreneurship Centre.
